We recommended to management the following: 

the Municipal Accountant to prepare journal entries to recognize the unrecorded Inventories amounting to ₱336,000.00;

comply with the provision of Section 2 of P.D. No. 1445.

We recommended to management the following: 

the Municipal Accountant to prepare adjusting entries to revert back all reclassified inventories to PPE accounts amounting to ₱10,170,487.22;

the Inventory Committee to include the reclassified inventories in their report on the physical count of PPEs to verify their existence;

to make separate schedules for PPE items costing less than ₱15,000.00 to facilitate the reclassification if deferment of GAM for LGUs will be lifted; and

comply with the provisions of IPSAS no. 12 and COA Circular no 2021-007.

We reiterated our previous audit recommendation that:

The Local Chief Executive and concerned municipal officials must ensure that at least 5% of the annual budget of the municipality can be attributed and utilized on GAD-related programs, projects and activities;

The members of the GAD Focal Point System and the Municipal Accountant to ensure availability of supporting documents necessary in the computation of actual GAD expenditures for further verification by this office;

The members of the GAD Focal Point System to undergo trainings on HGDG to strengthen their knowledge and capabilities in the conduct of gender analysis of programs and projects for purposes of GAD budget attribution; and

The members of the GAD Focal Point System to use monitoring tools such as the HGDG and PIMME in the GAD planning and budgeting as well as in the preparation of the accomplishment report.

